<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFAFFBBFC959AC36DD37BDE" blockId="23.[831,1437,1671,1887]" pageId="23" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFAFFBBFC959AC36ABD7BFE" bold="true" box="[831,944,1671,1695]" pageId="23" pageNumber="37">Remarks:</emphasis>
It resembles the specimens recorded by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) and SLITER (1968).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFAFFBBFC959A836D137A3E" blockId="23.[831,1437,1671,1887]" pageId="23" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFAFFBBFC959A836D627BBE" bold="true" box="[831,1135,1735,1759]" pageId="23" pageNumber="37">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in Campanian and Maastrichtian of Europe and North America (SLITER, 1969) and in the Maastrichtian of 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFFAFFBBFB139B436C357A7E" box="[1209,1336,1799,1823]" country="Egypt" name="Shamal Sina'" pageId="23" pageNumber="37">North Sinai</collectingRegion>
(SAID &amp; KENAWY, 1956). It is found in the Maastrichtian of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
